<paragraph blockId="88.[151,1436,226,492]" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,226,252]" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">Remarks:</emphasis>
All African species described so far are characterised by simple ventral clawlets on the claws on leg-I to -III, whereas the two species described from 
<collectingCountry box="[791,851,266,292]" name="India" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">India</collectingCountry>
bear comb-like ventral clawlets on the claws on leg-I to -III. The species can therefore be split into the species-groups of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="K. Viets" authorityYear="1914" box="[1048,1221,306,331]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Platymamersopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nordenskioeldi">
<emphasis box="[1048,1221,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">nordenskioeldi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-like species (simple clawlets, until now only known from Africa, named after 
<taxonomicName authority="K. Viets, 1914" authorityName="K. Viets" authorityYear="1914" box="[894,1282,346,372]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Platymamersopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nordenskioeldi">
<emphasis box="[894,1098,346,371]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">P. nordenskioeldi</emphasis>
K. 
<bibRefCitation author="Viets, K." box="[1146,1282,346,372]" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" pagination="341 - 388" refId="ref56377" refString="Viets, K. (1914) Hydracarinen-Fauna von Kamerun. Archiv fur Hydrobiologie, 9, 341 - 388." type="journal article" year="1914">Viets, 1914</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry name="Cameroon" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
) and the 
<emphasis box="[319,458,386,411]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">mysorensis-</emphasis>
like species (comb-like ventral clawlets, until now only known from 
<collectingCountry box="[1282,1345,386,412]" name="India" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">India</collectingCountry>
, named after 
<taxonomicName authority="Cook, 1967" authorityName="Cook" authorityYear="1967" box="[211,516,426,452]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Platymamersopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mysorensis">
<emphasis box="[211,372,426,451]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">P.mysorensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Cook" box="[375,516,426,452]" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" pagination="1 - 411" refId="ref55264" refString="Cook D. R. (1967) Water mites from India. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 9, 1 - 411." type="journal article" year="1967">Cook, 1967</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
). In the following three new species of each of these groups are described from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,295,466,492]" name="Madagascar" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
